  "text": "Immediately after administration, the animals were placed in metabolic cages (one animal per cage), specially designed to separate urine and feces, and cumulative urine output at 1, 2, 4, and 6 h was recorded. The diuretic activity was expressed in mL/100 g body weight [CITATION_1] , while the diuretic index was calculated as the ratio between the diuresis of the animals treated with the test substance and the diuresis of the control group [CITATION_2] .",
